rComments: Maybe Linear Algebra is partly to blame for my opinions about Prof. Bagnol, but I certainly didn't enjoy his class. He would repeat things 3-4 times a lecture, then claim they were different, and had a tendency to use terms and symbols without telling us what they meant. The tests were very easy as long as you put in the time to decipher his notes.

Ok prof, but his lectures can be pretty confusing since he just launches into a new chapter and starts using new terms/calculations left and right without even explaining what they mean or are supposed to do.  READ THE PROVIDED MANUAL.  The questions on the tests have been taken from/based on the manual so far.
le cours n'est pas compliqué en soi mais  on ne le comprend pas. on est confu dans son cours,il est dans son monde. les erreurs de calcul peuvent couter chères comme dans mon cas

Very decent prof. However, he was pretty disorganized; he rushed the last few weeks. If you took MAT1741, MAT2742 is really easy if you don't do stupid calculation errors (like I did) in exams. Therefore, had he taught a harder course, I'm not sure my rating would have been the same...
It's really hard for me to hear his sound and it results in a little bit confused for me.
